name Spaghetti with Bell Peppers and Pine Nuts
serves 3
tags main, pasta, vegetarian, italian

- 3 "red bell peppers"
- 3 "yellow bell peppers"
Quarter and deseed the peppers and place skin-side up on a baking sheet. Grill under the
broiler until the skin blackens and blisters. Transfer to a freezer bag and leave to cool.
Peel the peppers and cut into 2-3 cm pieces.
-> grilled peppers

- 3 cloves garlic
@nodep
Peel and finely dice the garlic.
-> garlic

- 3 "medium red chillies"
@nodep
Halve the chillies lengthways, deseed and finely dice.
-> chilli

- 100 g pine nuts
@nodep
Toast in a dry pan and set aside.
-> pine nuts

- 500 g spaghetti
@nodep
Cook in plenty of salted water until al dente, drain and keep warm.
-> spaghetti

- 10 tbsp olive oil
- "balsamic vinegar"
- salt
- pepper
= garlic
= chilli
= grilled peppers
= pine nuts
= spaghetti
Heat 2 tbsp of the oil in a pan. Gently sauté the garlic and chilli over low heat for
about 1 minute without letting them colour. Add the peppers, pine nuts, balsamic vinegar
and remaining oil and warm through. Toss with the hot spaghetti in a warmed bowl and
season with salt and pepper.

- 1 bunch basil
Tear the basil leaves into rough strips and carefully fold in.
